    97	8. **Optional cov ratchet 84 → 85** once `bootstrap.py` (79%) and `_commander_cli_helpers.py` (81%) gain edge-case tests.
    98	
    99	## Lifecycle rules
   100	
   101	1. **Before spawning a worker on a slice**, grep this file for the slice name. If a sibling exists and is clean, *resume that worktree* — do not create a new one.
   102	2. **Worktree create command** (parent only). Two layouts coexist (legacy + current); prefer the current `worktrees/` subdir layout for new work — Sprint 7h-14 standardised on it because it ringfences workers under one directory and keeps the repo siblings clean.
   103	
   104	   **Current convention (preferred — Sprint 7h-14+):**
   105	   ```bash
   106	   cd "/Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k"
   107	   mkdir -p "../worktrees"
   108	   git worktree add "../worktrees/cursor-<slug>" -b cursor/<slug> main
   109	   ```
   110	
   111	   **Legacy convention (sibling-of-SDK):**
   112	   ```bash
   113	   cd "/Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k"
   114	   git worktree add "../declarative-sdk-for-k-<slice>" -b <branch>
   115	   ```
   116	
   117	   Then append a row to this file with status `spawned <date> <owner>`.
   118	3. **On merge to `main`**, mark the row `MERGED <date> as <commit>`; do NOT delete the worktree until the parent has confirmed `main` carries the change in CI.
   119	4. **On abandon** (slice superseded / dead-end), mark `ABANDONED <date> reason=<one-line>` and `git worktree remove <path>` + `git branch -D <branch>` after parent confirms.
   120	5. **Never** force-push an active worker branch from the parent — coordinate with the worker owner first (or treat the branch as orphaned and abandon).
   121	6. **Never** add this file (or any orchestration file) to the SDK repo — it will be auto-pruned by the scope-fence.
   122	
   123	## Naming convention
   124	
   125	- Codex CLI runs: `codex/<area>-<phase>` (e.g. `codex/rotation-apply-v1`).
   126	- Cursor Composer/Task worker packs: `wp-<id>-<area>` (e.g. `wp-b-rotation-slice`).
   127	- Parent-driven branches: `cursor/<area>-<topic>` (e.g. `cursor/sdk-ksm-integration`).
   128	
   129	## Lessons captured from this multi-worktree push
   130	
   131	- Spawning more workers without tracking → duplicate work (`wp-b` ↔ `codex-rotation`, `wp-f` ↔ `codex-tuning`). Registry-first prevents.
   132	- Codex worktrees that finished offline-only design (no implementation) age into stale references; pin the next gate explicitly so they're either resumed or abandoned, not left to rot.
   133	- "Worker pack" (`wp-*`) and "Codex" (`codex/*`) naming co-existed without a convention — fixed above.
   134	- Files added to delivery repos that match the scope-fence globs disappear silently — keep orchestration coordination in the workspace parent (`Cursor tests/`) or the daybook mirror (`~/.cursor-daybook-sync/`), never in the delivery repo. (Lesson `[scope][drift]` 2026-04-26.)
   135	- **Sprint 7h-14:** Read-only Codex workers (decision memos, audits) parallelize trivially — share the primary worktree, dispatch via `codex_safe_launch.sh --repo "$SDK"`, harvest each worker's stdout from `/tmp/codex-offline-*-<pid>.log`. Wall time = max(per-worker), not sum. Write-mode workers still need a worktree per branch.
   136	- **Sprint 7h-14:** A merged PR doesn't always delete its remote branch — `gh pr merge --delete-branch` may be unset on some merges. Audit with `git ls-remote origin 'cursor/*' 'codex/*'` after every reconcile; cross-check against `gh pr list --state merged`; delete any merged-but-still-on-origin branch with `git push origin --delete <branch>`.
   137	- **Sprint 7h-14:** `codex_safe_launch.sh`'s `[[ -d "$REPO/.git" ]]` test fails on worktrees because `.git` is a regular file pointer there. Use `[[ -e .git ]]` followed by `git rev-parse --git-dir` to handle main + worktree layouts equally.

