     1	# Vault L1 — design (slice 1)
     2	
     3	**Status:** `DRAFT` — technical body **complete** for implementation (PR-V1+).
     4	Remove the `DRAFT` label and fill **§7** after integrator + reviewer sign-off.
     5	
     6	**Links:** [ORCHESTRATION_PAM_PARITY.md](./ORCHESTRATION_PAM_PARITY.md) §3 PR train ·
     7	[PAM_PARITY_PROGRAM.md](./PAM_PARITY_PROGRAM.md) ·
     8	[CONVENTIONS.md](../keeper_sdk/core/schemas/CONVENTIONS.md) ·
     9	[`keeper-vault.v1.schema.json`](../keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault/keeper-vault.v1.schema.json)
    10	
    11	---
    12	
    13	## 1. Scope (slice 1)
    14	
    15	### In scope (L1)
    16	
    17	- **`records[]`** only for this slice: each record has `uid_ref`, `type`, `title`,
    18	  optional `folder_ref`, optional `fields` / `custom` typed-field arrays, optional
    19	  `keeper_uid` (discover binding), optional `notes`.
    20	- **Record types:** start with **`login`** only (Commander `type` / template
    21	  alignment to be verified against pinned Commander). Adding other built-in types
    22	  is **L1.1** once `login` round-trips live.
    23	- **Empty sibling blocks:** `record_types[]`, `attachments[]`, and `keeper_fill`
    24	  may be **omitted or empty** in manifests; provider **must not** mutate them in
    25	  L1.
    26	- **Scale:** target first live proof with **≤ 5** declarative records in one
    27	  shared folder; no batch migration story in L1.
    28	
    29	### Out of scope until later slices
    30	
    31	- **`record_types[]`** CRUD, **attachments** binary workflow, **keeper_fill**
    32	  settings, rich payment/bank templates beyond what `login` needs.
    33	- **Generic / file / other** record kinds not explicitly listed in “In scope”.
    34	- **`keeper-vault-sharing.v1`** — see §5 (implemented **after** vault L1 is
    35	  stable on `main`).
    36	- Anything in [V2_DECISIONS.md](./V2_DECISIONS.md) **out-of-scope** list (MSP,
    37	  `convert`, `verify_records`, …).
    38	
    39	---
    40	
    41	## 2. Folder & identity
    42	
    43	### Folder scope
    44	
    45	- Same as PAM today: **`KEEPER_DECLARATIVE_FOLDER`** (or CLI `--folder-uid`)
    46	  identifies the shared folder where vault records are discovered and written.
    47	- **Slice 1 does not** support multi-folder vault manifests; `folder_ref` may
    48	  appear on records for **cross-family refs** per schema but L1 provider may
    49	  **reject** non-local folder targets with a clear `CapabilityError` until a memo
    50	  extends scope.
    51	
    52	### Manifest name (`build_plan` / diffs)
    53	
    54	- `keeper-vault.v1` JSON Schema currently has **no** top-level `name` key (unlike
    55	  legacy PAM `version`+`name`).
    56	- **Decision for L1:** use the **manifest file stem** as `manifest_name` when
    57	  wiring `build_plan` / ownership marker `manifest` field, until a schema
    58	  amendment adds optional `name:` (bundle that amendment with **V1** if product
    59	  prefers explicit names in YAML).
    60	
    61	### Ownership marker (parity with PAM)
    62	
    63	- **Reuse** [`MARKER_FIELD_LABEL`](../keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py)
    64	  (`keeper_declarative_manager`) and [`MANAGER_NAME`](../keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py)
    65	  (`keeper-pam-declarative`) so `decode_marker` / adoption logic stay unified.
    66	- **`resource_type` in marker JSON:** use the manifest record `type` string
    67	  (e.g. `login`) so mixed PAM + vault folders remain distinguishable in discover.
    68	- **`uid_ref`:** manifest `uid_ref` string (stable handle).
    69	- **`manifest`:** manifest name from previous bullet (stem or future `name:`).
