## Decision Memo: sharing.v1 3-Sprint Roadmap

### 0. Re-Baseline Flags

- **V6a/V6b are not landed in this checkout.** `sharing_diff.py` still says sibling diffs are deferred to 7h-41 and raises `NotImplementedError` for `shared_folders[]`, `share_records[]`, and `share_folders[]` live rows (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:5`, `keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:345`).
- **`WORKTREES.md` is parent-side, not in-repo**, by design (`../WORKTREES.md:5`). `LESSONS.md` is also outside this repo at `/Users/martin/Downloads/LESSONS.md`.
- This memo therefore treats 7h-42 as beginning from the actual tree: typed models + folder-only diff, no sharing CLI plan/apply, no sharing provider, no sharing live proof.

### 1. Current State Audit

- Schema status: `keeper-vault-sharing.v1` is still `scaffold-only`; evidence points to `docs/live-proof/README.md`; `since_pin` is `89047920a0df857e01fb59adcb0bfb9fa6db70bf` (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:6`).
- The sharing schema exposes four top-level blocks: `folders`, `shared_folders`, `share_records`, and `share_folders` (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:20`).
- For comparison, `keeper-vault.v1` is `supported`, with evidence at `docs/live-proof/keeper-vault.v1.91119c4.sanitized.json` and `since_pin` `91119c4e4f08139eec810ea6550abf92f8e79240` (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault/keeper-vault.v1.schema.json:6`).
- Vault’s evidence chain validates `validate -> plan -> apply -> discover -> verify -> re-plan -> destroy plan -> destroy apply -> re-discover` (`docs/live-proof/keeper-vault.v1.91119c4.sanitized.json:14`).
- Typed model coverage for sharing is all four blocks: `SharingManifestV1` has `folders`, `shared_folders`, `share_records`, and `share_folders` fields (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_models.py:172`).
- The `share_folders` model uses `kind` as the discriminator across `grantee`, `record`, and `default` variants (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_models.py:150`).
- Current diff coverage is **folders only**. The docstring says sibling blocks are deferred, and the public function enforces that with `NotImplementedError` (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:1`, `keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:340`).
- Current folder diff tests cover 12 folder-only cases; the only future-block test asserts `NotImplementedError` (`tests/test_sharing_diff_folders.py:72`, `tests/test_sharing_diff_folders.py:180`).
- Mock provider has only the generic `LiveRecord` store and generic `create/update/delete` handling (`keeper_sdk/providers/mock.py:24`, `keeper_sdk/providers/mock.py:56`). There is no sharing-specific round-trip test; existing mock round-trip evidence is vault-only (`tests/test_vault_mock_provider.py:29`).
- Commander provider has sharing-adjacent scaffold helpers only: `_ensure_folder_exists` calls `mkdir -uf`; `_ensure_shared_folder_exists` calls `mkdir -sf`; `_share_folder_to_ksm_app` calls `secrets-manager share add` (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1292`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1298`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1314`).
- The provider does not currently call `share-record` or `share-folder`; its documented command list covers PAM/vault commands and omits those share verbs (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:9`).
- CLI plan/apply dispatch is not wired for sharing: `load_declarative_manifest` supports PAM and vault only, and rejects other valid families (`keeper_sdk/core/manifest.py:88`, `keeper_sdk/core/manifest.py:129`).
- The CLI `_build_plan` branch is likewise PAM-or-vault only (`keeper_sdk/cli/main.py:693`, `keeper_sdk/cli/main.py:706`).
- Live-proof status for sharing is zero artifacts: the live-proof README still lists sharing as `scaffold-only` with “This README until a transcript lands” (`docs/live-proof/README.md:88`).
- Vault smoke currently covers only `records[]`: `_vault_one_login_manifest` returns `schema` plus one `records` entry (`scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:349`). The offline smoke test asserts the manifest keys are exactly `{"schema", "records"}` (`tests/test_smoke_vault_scenarios.py:51`).
- Sharing should not copy that sibling omission if the target is full-family `supported`; V2 defines sharing’s first-class blocks as all four top-level keys (`docs/V2_DECISIONS.md:21`).
- `WORKTREES.md` has no sharing-specific pending decision; current open items are KSM live proof and optional coverage ratchet (`../WORKTREES.md:88`, `../WORKTREES.md:95`).

### 2. Three-Gate Analysis

- Gate 1, schema annotation, is mechanical and last: live-proof README says to commit the artifact, then set status, evidence, and `since_pin` (`docs/live-proof/README.md:61`, `docs/live-proof/README.md:74`).
- Gate 2 requires mock + Commander provider support. The reusable rule is the three-gate lesson: schema status, provider slice, and live-proof transcript are separate gates (`/Users/martin/Downloads/LESSONS.md:416`).
- Commander method set needed:
  - `create_folder` / `create_shared_folder`: `mkdir` supports `-uf` and `-sf`, defaults, and color (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/folder.py:112`).
  - `move_folder`: `mv` supports source, destination, `--shared-folder`, and `--user-folder` selectors (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/folder.py:127`).
  - `delete_folder` / `delete_shared_folder`: `rmdir -f` removes a folder without prompting (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/folder.py:97`).
  - `share_record_to_user` / revoke: `share-record` supports email, grant/revoke, can-edit, can-share, recursive, and expiration (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:73`).
  - `share_folder_to_grantee`: `share-folder` supports user/team/default account via `-e`, plus manage-records/manage-users (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:92`).
  - `share_record_to_shared_folder`: `share-folder` supports record/default-record via `-r`, plus can-edit/can-share (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:98`).
  - `set_shared_folder_default_share`: Commander models default account and default record separately (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:310`, `.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:340`).
  - `discover_shared_folder_acl`: current smoke uses `get <sf_uid>` because Commander has no `share-folder --info` (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:252`).
- Gate 3 needs a `vaultSharingLifecycle` scenario using the existing smoke rhythm: validate, plan, apply, discover/verify, clean re-plan, destroy, final rediscover (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:327`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:404`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:413`).
- Minimum viable live scenario: create folders, shared folders, direct record shares, shared-folder grantee shares, shared-folder record shares, and default permissions. To truly cover all variants, use five `share_folders`: grantee-user, grantee-team, record, default-grantee, default-record. Four rows can cover the three outer subtypes, but not both default permission shapes (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:83`, `keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:188`).

### 3. Three-Sprint Slicing Recommendation

**Sprint 7h-42: provider parity**

- V7a: finish the missing diff/mock baseline first. Add sibling diff helpers for `shared_folders`, `share_records`, and `share_folders`, then extend mock state so all four blocks can create/update/delete and re-plan clean.
- V7a tests: separate round-trip tests per block, plus mixed-manifest test proving all four blocks survive apply/discover/re-plan.
- V7b: extend `CommanderCliProvider` with explicit sharing methods over `_run_cmd`, not direct DAG writes. Use stubbed `_run_cmd` tests for the exact argv from the Commander parser cited above.
- V7b must also add discovery normalization from `ls -f --format json`, `get <sf_uid>`, and record `get` output; current sandbox already proves those surfaces are used for smoke (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:219`, `scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:252`).
- V7c: wire `keeper-vault-sharing.v1` into `load_declarative_manifest`, `PlanLoadBundle`, `_build_plan`, `_make_provider`, and CLI plan/apply. Current dispatch rejects non-PAM/non-vault families (`keeper_sdk/core/manifest.py:131`).

**Sprint 7h-43: smoke scenario design**

- V8a: add `SharingScenarioSpec` or equivalent next to `VaultScenarioSpec` (`scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:335`).
- V8a fixture: roughly 10 folders, 2 shared folders, 3 direct `share_records`, and 5 `share_folders` if the goal is complete subtype proof.
- V8a verifier: assert ACL rows, default permissions, parent folder placement, and no drift rows after rediscovery. Existing vault verifier’s “compute diff again and fail on create/update/conflict” pattern is reusable (`scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:402`).
- V8b: offline tests must validate manifest shape, typed load, expected diff rows, mock apply, and clean re-plan.
- V8c: reuse profile locks. The harness already locks by tenant, profile, admin config, shared-folder title, KSM app, and project name (`scripts/smoke/README.md:174`).

**Sprint 7h-44: live proof + supported bump**

- V9a: run `python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario vaultSharingLifecycle --login-helper env` under the granted live harness discipline. Capture sanitized JSON at `docs/live-proof/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.<pin>.sanitized.json`.
- V9b: bump schema status to `supported`, evidence to that artifact, and `since_pin` to the full `.commander-pin` SHA, following the live-proof checklist (`docs/live-proof/README.md:74`).
- V9b meta-test: assert schema annotation status/evidence/since_pin match the committed artifact and full 40-char pin.
- V9c readonly: completion memo for sharing.v1, with anti-patterns for the next family. V2 identifies `keeper-enterprise.v1` as the next family after sharing (`docs/V2_DECISIONS.md:25`).

### 4. Parent-Decide Items

- Discriminator field: keep `kind`. Schema variants each have a `kind` const, and the typed model uses `Field(discriminator="kind")` (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:161`, `keeper_sdk/core/sharing_models.py:150`).
- Subtype switch: no V6b choice is visible in this checkout. Commander does not mutate a grantee share into a record share in place; it builds separate user/team and record update/remove queues (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:438`, `.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:538`).
- Therefore actual tenant semantics are delete+create. But for the **same `uid_ref`** subtype switch, emit `CONFLICT` unless the planner gains replacement ordering; current `Plan.ordered()` runs creates/updates before deletes (`keeper_sdk/core/planner.py:72`).
- Default share collision: assert at most one default row per `(shared_folder_uid_ref, target)`. Commander has one account-default surface and one record-default surface, so two defaults for the same target should be a diff conflict, while one `grantee` default plus one `record` default is valid (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:428`, `.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:534`).

### 5. Risks And Mitigations

- Commander sharing commands may be flaky under live auth/session behavior. Budget one minimal self-fix pass in V9a; the vault live-proof lesson explicitly allows one in-run fix with honest transcript notes (`/Users/martin/Downloads/LESSONS.md:431`).
- Sandbox cleanup currently removes SDK-marked records only, then optionally removes the sandbox shared folder (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:113`, `scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:137`). Add marker-guarded ACL revocation for sharing destroy so shared-folder record/user ACLs do not survive after record cleanup.
- Marker storage: use markers on marker-bearing folder/shared-folder objects only. The marker contract is a custom field value (`keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py:17`), and current sharing folder diff already reads marker/custom/custom_fields (`keeper_sdk/core/sharing_diff.py:50`).
- Do not try to mark `share_records` or `share_folders` directly; those are relational rows tied to `record_uid_ref` and `shared_folder_uid_ref` in the schema (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:138`, `keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:150`).
- Team-grantee proof may need a pre-existing enterprise team or an enterprise-family setup dependency. If no stable team exists in the lab tenant, make team-grantee an explicit V9 blocker instead of silently treating user-grantee as full coverage.

### 6. Candidate Lesson

`2026-04-27 [roadmap][per-family-3-sprint-template] Audit the three gates first, then land provider parity, smoke shape, and live-proof+schema bump as separate sprints; no family claims supported until schema annotation, mock/Commander provider, and sanitized clean re-plan all cross-cite.`
